# dictator MQTT credentials for the broker auth cutover (provisioning/broker-auth-cutover.md).
# Copy to instance/mqtt.env (gitignored, chmod 600) and fill in the password you set with
# mosquitto_passwd for the `dictator` user. Every server MQTT service reads these via
# EnvironmentFile=-.../instance/mqtt.env (see systemd/ha-{scanner,writer,edge-mapper}.service)
# and applies them through server/util/mqtt_creds.py:apply_credentials().
#
# Latent-safe: harmless on today's anonymous broker; becomes the live identity at cutover step 5.
HA_MQTT_USER=dictator
HA_MQTT_PASS=CHANGE_ME
